events.name: Patrick DeGuire
events.description: Patrick DeGuire started performing stand up after losing a significant amount of vision. He discovered laughter to be therapeutic. He won the Improv Harrah?s National Comedy Club Talent Search. This led to appearances on Comedy Central and Comics Unleashed. He has also been heard on The Bob and Tom Show and NPR. Patrick has toured with Tom Segura and Theo Von and Gabriel Iglesias. He has performed for U.S. troops in numerous countries including Iraq and Japan and South Korea. His material explores the advantages and disadvantages of living with limited vision. He discusses the challenges of relationships and being a father to eight children. Patrick headlines top comedy clubs throughout the United States. His perspective on life is both insightful and hilarious. He addresses an assortment of topics that resonate with diverse audiences. Patrick continues to be a favorite in the national comedy scene.

events.description: Ahmed Ahmed is an Egyptian American actor and comedian. He is also a producer and director. He is known as a multi faceted talent in the industry. Ahmed co founded the Axis of Evil Comedy Tour. This tour aired on Comedy Central and traveled across the Middle East. He has filmed two comedy specials for Showtime. He starred in the series Sullivan and Son on TBS. His acting credits include Iron Man, Weeds, Swingers and You Don?t Mess with the Zohan. Ahmed directed the award winning documentary Just Like Us. This film premiered at the Tribeca Film Festival. It won many awards for best director and best documentary. Ahmed even dined with President Obama at the White House because of his work. He can be seen in the documentary Too Soon on Vice TV. He is currently developing new television shows and films. Ahmed believes that laughter heals. He thinks comedy bridges the gap between communities worldwide.

events.description: James Walker is a famous American actor and comedian. He was born in 1947 and raised in the Bronx. Walker earned two Golden Globe nominations for this role. Time Magazine named him the comedian of the decade for the 1970s. He helped launch the careers of Jay Leno and David Letterman by hiring them as writers. He has appeared in films like Airplane and Let is Do It Again. He continues to perform stand up around the world today. He has written a best selling book and recorded two Grammy nominated albums. He remains a beloved figure in television history.
